children.text: The under-floor insulation has not been installed, which will be reducing the effectiveness of the thermal performance.
elevant Australian Standard AS 3900 Bulk Thermal Insulation states in section 5.5.2.1 Suspended Floors that
‘Bulk insulation shall be installed in suspended floors to form a thermal barrier between conditioned and unconditioned spaces’ .
The insulation in these areas must be installed to ensure thermal performance prior to the plaster installation.
